A Favorite in Mexico, Simple Entomatadas with Fried Eggs

Entomatadas are tortillas bathed in a tomato sauce! They are very popular in Oaxaca, Mexico for breakfast. They are served with eggs or a jerky like meat from that region.  I made them for breakfast today and I had forgotten how delicious they are.  Literally, I had them made in less than 30 minutes.  You could make the sauce the day before, double the recipe and freeze so that next time it's a matter of heating and softening the tortillas in hot oil and folding. Click the link for the recipe:

://the2spoons.com/simple-entomatadas-with-fried-eggs/

Just because it’s not summer, doesn’t mean you can’t get some sweet and juicy tomatoes. Like these heirloom tomatoes I got the other day from @central_market! What better way to eat them than on a tomato sandwich or in this case, an open  face sandwich topped with scrambled eggs and fresh herbs. To make, butter a good quality bread on both sides. I used a high protein bread from the bakery at the store. Then toast in a griddle or in a skillet on both sides, slather mayonnaise over one side. Add your sliced tomatoes and lightly  salt and pepper. Soft scramble your eggs and place them on top of your tomatoes. You could add cheese of your choice. Grated parmesan would be great! Such a delicious quick breakfast! #breakfast #eggs #scrambledeggs #heirloom #tomatoes #herbs #toast @central_market

Happy Thanksgiving from The 2 spoons! Hoping you are having a wonderful day with family and friends, and that your home is filled with laughter and love as you prepare for this very special meal together. 

Some of my favorite memories were growing up with my Mom in the kitchen making the most wonderful Turkey and Dressing for our family of 7.  She made the most delicious Southern Cornbread dressing.  Until she passed away at 93 she still was the official Dressing taster!  I still don’t think mine is as good as hers was, and her mothers, and her mothers. It’s a recipe passed down from generation to generation. 

 if you are alone I pray you have peace and you too are able to enjoy a delicious meal. I know holidays are lonely for some. Cook yourself a special meal, order out, go to a restaurant, watch Christmas movies on Hallmark. Even alone we can find joy and happiness. 

On to what to do with those leftovers? I have the perfect solution! I’ve done this for years and it’s always a hit! As you can see, I’ve made them many different ways over the years! 

Here’s the link and let me know how your pot pie turns out! 
I actually have two recipes. One for Turkey Pot Pie and the other is Chicken Pot pie that you can substitute Turkey.
